               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donor; &#xD;
elements of the punctuation signs;&#xD;
elements of Ethiopic numbers;&#xD;
the word sälam.&#xD;
A few lines, divided into several groups alternating with black lines, in the pages opening the commemoration notes for each month: &#xD;
10 lines for the month of Mäggabit (fol. 7r); &#xD;
8 lines for the months of Miyazya (fol. 36r), Säne (fol. 84r) and Ḥamle (fol. 110r); &#xD;
6 lines for the months of Gǝnbot (fol. 57v), Näḥase (fol. 148v) and Ṗagwǝmen (fol. 173v).&#xD;
The first two lines of the first commemoration note of the day, one (sometimes two) line of all other commemoration notes.&#xD;
One line of the concluding formula for the month of Miyazya (fol. 57rc, l.1);&#xD;
two lines of the concluding formula for the month of Näḥase (fol. 173rabc, ls. 12-13).</rubric>
